  <datafield tag="351" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="3">Videos, web archives, and paper production materials</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">Arranged into four series: 1. Arts, Culture, and Entertainment. 2. Education, Health, and Social Issues. 3. Fundraising and Marketing. 4. Web Archives.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In English.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Sue Marx is a celebrated documentary filmmaker whose career in Detroit spanned more than thirty years and included an Academy Award victory for her 1987 short subject "Young at Heart." Working first with Detroit's WWJ-TV on its lauded "Profiles in Black," Marx later established her own studio, which produced numerous acclaimed promotional videos, public service pieces, retrospective films, and documentaries about local organizations and causes.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Materials (mostly audio-visual) pertaining to films produced by Sue Marx, almost exclusively those created during her career as an independent filmmaker. Collection includes final versions of films, raw footage, background and research information, and other components of Marx's documentaries.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection is open for research use.</subfield>
  </datafield>
